entry.title: This is an Alberta Emergency Alert. Strathcona County is issuing an evacuation alert.
entry.summary:
A large grassfire is burning in this area.

entry.title: This is an Alberta Emergency Alert. Strathcona County is issuing an evacuation order.

Area: (Western boundary of evacuation zone is Marlboro and Range Road 200 all the way to the East of Yellowhead County. Northern boundary is Township Road 550 and southern is Township Road 520. This includes the town of Edson.)

entry.title: This is an Alberta Emergency Alert. Yellowhead County has updated the Evacuation Order for immediate evacuation for the east part of Yellowhead County.
entry.summary: Evacuation Order for immediate evacuation for the east part of Yellowhead County. Fire conditions have increased. If you have not left, you must leave immediately. Head west on Highway 16 to get to the reception centre in Edson. Fire has jumped the River from Parkland in Yellowhead County and is moving fast in a westerly direction. Area: (This is for the east part of Yellowhead County. The evacuation area starts at the Pembina River west to Range Road 101. North border is Township Road 550 and south border to Township Road 520. Includes Evansburg, Wildwood, Lobstick, Hansonville.)

entry.title: This is an Alberta Emergency Alert. Leduc County has updated a wildfire alert.
entry.summary:
The wildfire remains contained and crews are on scene monitoring for flare ups. High winds are anticipated this afternoon, which may cause conditions to deteriorate quickly.
The evacuation of the area is still in effect.
Range Road 40 between Township Road 494 and Township Road 495 is closed. Area: (This alert is in effect for everyone from Range Road 41 east to Range Road 35 and from Township Road 494 north to Township Road 495. The affected area is approximately 4 miles north and 5 miles west of the Village of Warburg in Leduc County.)
